Text: The Kissyoung Marine and his commanding officer board a train headed through the mountains of Switzerland They can find no place to sit except for two seats right across the aisle from a young woman and her grandmother After a while it is obvious that the young woman and the young soldier are interested in each other because they are giving each other looks Soon the train passes into a tunnel and it is pitch black There is a sound of the smack of a kiss followed by the sound of the smack of a slap When the train emerges from the tunnel the four sit there without saying a word The grandmother is thinking to herself It was very brash for that young soldier to kiss my granddaughter but Im glad she slapped him The commanding officer is setting there thinking I didnt know the young Marine was brave enough to kiss the girl but I sure wish she hadnt missed him when she slapped and hit me The young woman was sitting and thinking Im glad the soldier kissed me but I wish my grandmother had not slapped him The young Marine sat there with a satisfied smile on his face thinking to himself Life is good When does a fellow have the chance to kiss a beautiful girl and slap his commanding officer all at the same time

The New Maidsingle man wanted someone to help him with the household chores so he decided to get a pet to help out He went to the local pet shop and asked the owner for advice on a suitable animal The owner suggested a dog but the man said Nah dogs cant do dishes The owner then suggested a cat but the man said Nah cats cant do the ironing Finally the owner suggests a centipede This is the perfect pet for you It can do anything OK the man thought Ill give it a try so he bought it and took it home Once home he told the centipede to wash the dishes The centipede looks over and there are piles and piles of dirty dishes that look to be a month old Five minutes later all the pots are washed dried and put away Great thought the man Now he told the centipede to do the dusting and vacuuming Fifteen minutes later the house is spotless Wow thought the man so he decided to try another idea Go down to the corner and get me the evening paper he told the centipede and off it went Fifteen minutes later the centipede hadnt returned minutes later and still no centipede Fortyfive minutes and the man was sick of waiting so he got up and went out to look for the centipede As he opened the front door there on the step was the centipede Hey whatcha doing there I sent you out for the paper minutes ago and now I find you out here without the paper What gives Hold on a minute said the centipede Im still putting on my boots

Update Contributionsyou would like to contribute to the fund for Bob please have your donation to me before pm today We have decided to donate the money in memory of his Grandmother to the nursing home she had lived in for the past years I will also be filling out the form for Enrons Gift Matching Program A small portion of the money will be for a plaque for Bob that will be engraved with language regarding our donation Bob does not know about this I will get the plaque over the weekend and we can present it to Bob sometime next week Becky Forwarded by Becky TlucekHOUECT on PM Becky Tlucek PM To Roger CT Peggy CT Sandi M CT Shonnie CT Shawna CT Barbara N CT Jeffrey T CT Dan J CT Gerald CT Steve Van CT Kimberlee A CT Matt NRON Mary CT Erica CT Pat CT Jenny ct Kaye CT cc bcc Becky TlucekHOUECT Subject Update Bob Walkers Grandmother Update Today there will be a full dinner delivered to the Walker household from the ENA Legal Department The Walkers know there will be a delivery but do not know what it is I will still be accepting contributions for a gift from those who work closely with Bob that would like to do something on a more personal level Becky Forwarded by Becky TlucekHOUECT on PM Becky Tlucek AM To Roger CT Peggy CT Sandi M CT Shonnie CT Shawna CT Barbara N CT Jeffrey T CT Dan J CT Gerald CT Steve Van CT Kimberlee A CT Matt NRON Mary CT Erica CT Pat CT Jenny ct Kaye CT cc Subject Bob Walkers Grandmother Bob Walkers Grandmother passed away over the weekend The funeral was Monday We are going to get a gift certificate to Lubys for Bob and his wife to enjoy an evening dinner and depending on funds possibly a plant or flowers If you would like to contribute please see me A card will be circulated shortly Becky

Donations for Bobcall for donations for Bobs Grandmothers fund We are donating the monies collected to the nursing home Bobs Grandmother lived in An engraved plaque will be given to Bob and his wife as a remembrance of our and Enrons matching donation I will be picking up the plaque tonight after work A heartfelt thank you to those of you who have contributed thus far I know Bob will be touched Becky PS To my knowledge Bob is not aware that we are doing this Lets keep it a surprise if we can

Update Bob Walkers Grandmother Fundthe donations I received for Bob we were able to purchase an engraved plaque as a momento for Bob of our donation to the Baptist Memorial Center the nursing home Bobs Grandmother lived in for the past years Since this is a very emotional time I quietly gave Bob the plaque and card right before lunch today You may drop by to see it at your discretion He was extremely touched I am waiting to mail the donation until later this week because I have a feeling there is still one or two people who may want to contribute and have been too busy to do so Thank you again to everyone for keeping Bob and his family in your thoughts and prayers Becky
